Project: Swamp Fox Command Center
Build a full internal dashboard for Swamp Fox Agency, a commercial insurance agency specializing in trucking and logging risks (Moncks Corner, SC).

Tech Stack
Frontend: React + TypeScript, scaffolded with Vite
Styling: Tailwind CSS
Charts/Visuals: Power BI Embedded (powerbi-client + powerbi-client-react)
Auth: Mock token service now, wire to Azure AD (service principal) later
Deployment: Local intranet (localhost dev, production via IIS or local Node server)
Branding — match swampfoxagency.com exactly
Primary accent: #2ea3f2 (bright blue)
Dark base: #2d3940 (dark blue-gray)
Headings: #333333
Body text: #666666
Main background: #ffffff
Panel/alternate background: #f3f3f3
Dividers/borders: #e2e2e2
Font: Inter or clean sans-serif
File Structure — Feature-based

swamp-fox-command-center/
  src/
    features/
      dashboard/        ← Home/Overview: KPI tiles, high-level metrics
      policies/         ← Active policies, renewals, lapsed accounts
      claims/           ← Open claims, loss ratios, trends
      drivers/          ← Driver records (heavy auto liability / trucking focus)
    components/         ← Shared UI (Sidebar, TopBar, Layout)
    services/
      auth.ts           ← Mock token service (stub Azure AD later)
      powerbi.ts        ← Power BI embed config stub
    hooks/
    context/
      AuthContext.tsx
    types/
    App.tsx
    main.tsx
Pages (4 at launch)
Home / Overview — KPI summary tiles
Policies — Active policies, renewals due, lapsed
Claims — Open claims, loss ratios, trends
Drivers — Driver records and auto liability metrics (trucking/auto liability is a core book)
Power BI Integration
Now: Styled placeholder panels (no real embed yet)
Later: Wire in real workspace/report IDs and embed tokens via Power BI REST API + Azure AD service principal
Data Source
All data lives in Microsoft Fabric, surfaced through Power BI Embedded via the Power BI REST API.

Project Location
